Many have expressed displeasure at Neymar’s excessive rolling on the pitch after being fouled and have called for stern action against him from referees. JOHANNESBURG - Football fans across the world have reacted to Brazil forward Neymar over his diving antics that have been on display during this year’s World Cup in Russia. Many have expressed displeasure at Neymar’s excessive rolling on the pitch after being fouled and have called for stern action against him from referees. Neymar has scored two goals in this World Cup so far, one of them against a plucky Mexico side in the round of 16 clash to book a quarter-final meeting with Belgium who beat a spirited Japan side 3-2.   